This is an EXAMPLE key block for demonstration purposes.
Real PGP keys are much longer and contain actual cryptographic data.

Generate a real test key with:
  gpg --batch --gen-key <<EOF
  %no-protection
  Key-Type: RSA
  Key-Length: 2048
  Name-Real: Test User
  Name-Email: test@example.com
  Expire-Date: 1y
  %commit
  EOF

Then export with:
  gpg --armor --export-secret-keys test@example.com

